---
title: Kedjeree Style Rice with Smoked Haddock and Green Beans
description: Kedgeree is a brilliant example of an Anglo-Indian culinary mash up, having started its life as ‘khichari’, a spiced Indian dish of rice and lentils. Traditionally enjoyed for breakfast, chef Mimi decided to give this flavoursome dish her own twist, subbing out hard boiled eggs in favour of crunchy stir-fried green beans, to make it the perfect dinner time dish. Breakfast for dinner? It’s a yes from us!
